## Never Copy Mutexes

**Copying a mutex creates a separate lock with no synchronization.** Always pass structs containing mutexes by pointer.

```go
// ✅ Good: Pass by pointer
func process(d *Data) {
    d.mu.Lock()
    defer d.mu.Unlock()
    d.value++
}

// ❌ Bad: Copy passes a different mutex
func process(d Data) {  // d is a copy
    d.mu.Lock()  // Locks the copy, not the original—no synchronization!
    defer d.mu.Unlock()
}
```

**Tip:** Run `go vet`—it detects mutex copying.

