## Use RWMutex for Read-Heavy Workloads

**sync.RWMutex** allows multiple concurrent readers or a single writer. Use when reads vastly outnumber writes.

```go
// ✅ Good: RWMutex for read-heavy cache
type ConfigCache struct {
    mu   sync.RWMutex
    cfg  map[string]Config
}

func (c *ConfigCache) Get(key string) (Config, bool) {
    c.mu.RLock()
    defer c.mu.RUnlock()
    cfg, ok := c.cfg[key]
    return cfg, ok
}

func (c *ConfigCache) Set(key string, cfg Config) {
    c.mu.Lock()
    defer c.mu.Unlock()
    c.cfg[key] = cfg
}

// ⚠️ RWMutex cannot upgrade: RLock → Lock is deadlock
// Must release RLock before acquiring Lock
```

