## Minimize Critical Section Duration

**Hold locks only as long as necessary.** Avoid I/O, network calls, or expensive computation while holding a lock.

```go
// ✅ Good: Minimize critical section
func (s *Service) GetAndProcess(key string) (Result, error) {
    s.mu.RLock()
    data, ok := s.cache[key]
    s.mu.RUnlock()  // Release before expensive work

    if !ok {
        return Result{}, ErrNotFound
    }
    return expensiveProcessing(data), nil  // Outside lock
}

// ❌ Bad: I/O inside critical section
func (s *Service) GetAndProcess(key string) (Result, error) {
    s.mu.Lock()
    defer s.mu.Unlock()
    data := s.cache[key]
    result := callExternalAPI(data)  // Blocking I/O while holding lock!
    return result, nil
}
```

