## Establish Consistent Lock Ordering

**Acquiring locks in different orders across goroutines causes deadlock.** Establish a canonical order (e.g., by resource ID, by fixed convention) and always acquire in that order.

```go
// ✅ Good: Consistent lock order (e.g., by ID)
func (s *Service) Transfer(fromID, toID int, amount int) error {
    if fromID > toID {
        fromID, toID = toID, fromID  // Canonical order
    }
    from := s.getAccount(fromID)
    to := s.getAccount(toID)
    from.mu.Lock()
    defer from.mu.Unlock()
    to.mu.Lock()
    defer to.mu.Unlock()
    // ...
}

// ❌ Bad: Different order in different code paths
func transfer(a, b *Account, amount int) {
    a.mu.Lock()
    b.mu.Lock()
    // ...
}
func swap(a, b *Account) {
    b.mu.Lock()  // Different order—deadlock risk!
    a.mu.Lock()
    // ...
}
```

