## Encapsulate Shared State

**Protect all access to shared data within struct methods that handle locking.** Don't expose raw mutex or unlocked access.

```go
// ✅ Good: Encapsulated access
type SafeCounter struct {
    mu    sync.Mutex
    value int
}

func (c *SafeCounter) Inc() {
    c.mu.Lock()
    defer c.mu.Unlock()
    c.value++
}

func (c *SafeCounter) Value() int {
    c.mu.Lock()
    defer c.mu.Unlock()
    return c.value
}

// ❌ Bad: Exposing unlocked field
type BadCounter struct {
    mu    sync.Mutex
    Value int  // Exported—callers can bypass lock
}
```

---

## Consider sync/atomic for Simple Counters

**For simple counters or flags, `sync/atomic` may be more appropriate than a mutex.**

```go
// ✅ Good: atomic for simple counter
type Counter struct {
    value atomic.Int64
}

func (c *Counter) Inc() {
    c.value.Add(1)
}

func (c *Counter) Value() int64 {
    return c.value.Load()
}
```

